The course provides students with extended knowledge of the biology of Estonian games; methods and principles for their economic utilisation. Overview is given of the state of games, major research methods of the respective applied studies and problems in Estonia, Nordic countries and Baltic countries in general.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The goal of the wildlife biology  course is to bring together the principles of 
ecology, population biology, wildlife conservation and management.  It also focuses
on the status, population analysis and problems in the context of  local game
species. It considers the problems of conservation and management from Nordic,
Baltic and Estonian points of view.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students should be able to analyze and interpret different available information to produce meaningful conclusions and give recommendations for  wildlife conservation and management.  In the process they also need to aquire knowledge about the statuses of game animals , population analysis and problems in the context of  local game species. They also will be aware of the conservation and management problems in other regions.
